-- Colombian Stocks: Bancolombia, Davivienda, Colinversiones
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2012-01-30T15:20:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-30/colombian-stocks-bancolombia-davivienda-colinversiones.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:51 a.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  gained 0.3 percent to 13,641.73, while the
Colcap Index advanced 0.3 percent to 1,599.79.  Banco Davivienda SA (PFDAVVND)  , Colombia’s third-biggest
bank, rose 0.6 percent to 19,640 pesos. The bank is offering
investors the option of converting as much as half of their
common shares into preferred shares, according to a Jan. 27
regulatory filing.  Bancolombia SA (BCOLO)  , Colombia’s biggest lender, rose
1 percent to 26,160 pesos. The bank said it sold 44.4 million
shares for 1.2 billion pesos ($661,000), according to a Jan. 27
regulatory filing.  The bank said Jan. 5 it planned to sell as much as 1.66
trillion pesos of shares. Stock that wasn’t sold in  Colombia 
will be offered abroad as level 3 American depositary receipts
in a sale handled by  UBS Investment Bank , Bank of America,
Merrill Lynch and JP Morgan, the filing said.  Cia. Colombiana de Inversiones SA  (COLINV CB), a Colombian
electricity holding company, advanced 2.4 percent to 4,550
pesos, a four-month high. The company signed a contract with a
unit of Integral SA to acquire Produccion de Energia SAS, which
was given rights to develop the 352-megawatt Porvenir II
hydroelectric project in the Antioquia region, according to a
Jan. 27 regulatory filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
